  "title": "react-dom@15.4.1 breaks build 🚨",
  "body": "Hello lovely humans,\n\n[react-dom](https://www.npmjs.com/package/react-dom) just published its new version 15.4.1.\n\n<table>\n  <tr>\n    <th align=left>\n      State\n    </th>\n    <td>\n      Failing tests :rotating_light:\n    </td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <th align=left>\n      Dependency\n    </td>\n    <td>\n      react-dom\n    </td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <th align=left>\n      New version\n    </td>\n    <td>\n      15.4.1\n    </td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <th align=left>\n      Type\n    </td>\n    <td>\n      dependency\n    </td>\n  </tr>\n</table>\n\nThis version is **covered** by your **current version range** and after updating it in your project **the build went from success to failure**.\n\nAs react-dom is a direct dependency of this project **this is very likely breaking your project right now**. If other packages depend on you it’s very likely also breaking them.\nI recommend you give this issue a very high priority. I’m sure you can resolve this :muscle:\n\n\nOf course this could just be a false positive, caused by a flaky test suite, or third parties that are currently broken or unavailable, but that would be another problem I’d recommend working on.\n\n\nDo you have any ideas how I could improve these pull requests? Did I report anything you think isn’t right?\nAre you unsure about how things are supposed to work?\n\nThere is a collection of [frequently asked questions](https://greenkeeper.io/faq.html) and while I’m just a bot, there is a group of people who are happy to teach me new things. [Let them know](https://github.com/greenkeeperio/greenkeeper/issues/new).\n\nGood luck with your project :sparkles:\n\nYou rock!\n\n:palm_tree:\n\n---\n[GitHub Release](https://github.com/facebook/react/releases/tag/v15.4.1)\n\n<h3>React</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Restructure variable assignment to work around a Rollup bug (<a href=\"https://urls.greenkeeper.io/gaearon\">@gaearon</a> in <a href=\"https://urls.greenkeeper.io/facebook/react/pull/8384\">#8384</a>)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>React DOM</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed event handling on disabled button elements (<a href=\"https://urls.greenkeeper.io/spicyj\">@spicyj</a> in <a href=\"https://urls.greenkeeper.io/facebook/react/pull/8387\">#8387</a>)</li>\n<li>Fixed compatibility of browser build with AMD environments (<a href=\"https://urls.greenkeeper.io/zpao\">@zpao</a> in <a href=\"https://urls.greenkeeper.io/facebook/react/pull/8374\">#8374</a>)</li>\n</ul>\n\n---\nThis pull request was created by [greenkeeper.io](https://greenkeeper.io/).\n\n<sub>Tired of seeing this sponsor message? :zap: `greenkeeper upgrade`</sub>",
